{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/6273", "repo": "rails", "body": "@rafaelfranca I took the time and tested your assumption and it turns out that rails will *trust* anything you pass as the name into `content_tag`.\n\nFor example:\n\n```ruby\n\n>> helper.content_tag(\"/div><script>alert('ZOMG')</script>\")\n=> \"</div><script>alert('ZOMG')</script>><//div><script>alert('ZOMG')</script>>\"\n```\n\nI made a commit here:\nhttps://github.com/KensoDev/rails/commit/ad2a80e8b86a638e180b36db065022c40645a74c\n\nThis is a first attempt to attack the issue on securing the tag, I am not sure if this is viable or not, or if we want to go down that path.\n\nIf we secure this input, we can make the `simple_format` function accept any input to the `:wrapper_tag` option I wanted to add.\n\nWhat do you think?\n\ncc/ @tenderlove ", "_id": {"$oid": "523e69b5bd354364b900feb2"}, "issue_id": 6273, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/5678518", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/6273#issuecomment-5678518", "updated_at": "2012-05-13T19:01:02Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KensoDev/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KensoDev/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KensoDev/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KensoDev/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/KensoDev", "login": "KensoDev", "gravatar_id": "b7d890bed68fa564c18ff00dfd8207cd", "html_url": "https://github.com/KensoDev", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KensoDev/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KensoDev/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KensoDev/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/b7d890bed68fa564c18ff00dfd8207cd?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Ffccc1b57686a6f60a13900c645aac4c1.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KensoDev/star